      • replicationFailureMaxRetryAttempts

        public static int replicationFailureMaxRetryAttempts
        While Online and Authenticated, if replication is encountering continuous errors, after this number of consecutive errors replication will be paused for a period of time as specified by PredixMobilityConfiguration.replicationFailureRetryRecoveryTime. Changes to connectivity state will reset the error count.

      • replicationFailureRetryRecoveryTime

        public static int replicationFailureRetryRecoveryTime
        After PredixMobilityConfiguration.replicationFailureRetryAttempts have been surpased, replication will pause for this time interval before resuming. Changes to connectivity state will invalidate the timer.

      • seriousErrorPage

        public static java.lang.String seriousErrorPage
        The Bundled HTML filename used for the catastrophic error display that is shown to the user when no webapp can be loaded or the application cannot otherwise continue. If this file is not found a native UI alert message will be used.

      • appendDataViewDefinition

        public static void appendDataViewDefinition(DBViewDefinition view)
        Allows you to add a database view to the underlying Predix mobile storage system. Views contain map and/or reduce functions which alter the projection of data in storage.
        Parameters:
        view - a DBViewDefinition which alters the projection of documents in the underlying predix mobile storage engine.

      • appendReplicationChannel

        public static void appendReplicationChannel(java.lang.String channel)
        Adds a channel to the existing set of channels on pull replication.
        Parameters:
        channel - A String containing the name of a channel to be included during replication.

      • removeReplicationChannel

        public static void removeReplicationChannel(java.lang.String channel)
        Removes a channel from the existing set of channels on pull replication.
        Parameters:
        channel - A String containing the name of a channel to be removed from replication.

      • addNewFilter

        public static void addNewFilter(java.lang.String filterName,
                                PushReplicationFilter filter)
        This method is sed to add a new PushReplicationFilter to the underlying Predix Mobile storage engine. These filters can restrict certain documents from being replicated to the Predix Mobile Service.
        Parameters:
        filterName - A String indicating the name of the filter.
        filter - A PushReplicationFilter which restricts certain documents from replicating.

      • loadConfiguration

        public static void loadConfiguration()
        Called internally by the system to load all of the configuration files and preferences. These contain the settings that control which endpont the system will authenticate and communicate with as well as which PM app to load on startup.
